Testing specs draft
Retry coming up on my bot
DCR: As a DevOps engineer, I would like to see some documentation on how to integrate tests in the Azure DevOps CI and CD pipelines so I can ensure the bot doesn't break before I publish it
DCR: As a tester, I would like to be able to load test my bot to ensure it can handle the expected number of users without overloading the Bot Service infrastructure
DCR: As a Support engineer, I'd like to be able to execute periodic tests that would alert me if the bot or related services are not working or they are degraded
DCR: As a tester, I would like to be able to record an exploratory test session and be able to submit a bug with a transcript of that session so the developers can run the repro and fix the error
DCR: As a tester, I would like to be able to create transcript files and execute them against a deployed bot to ensure the conversation goes as expected
DCR: As a developer, I would like to see some documentation to understand how to use the DialogTestClient provided by the framework so I can write unit tests for my bot
DCR: As a Support engineer, I'd like to be able to create a work item in Azure DevOps when a production bot throws an alert
DCR: As a tester, I would like to be able to create a work item in Azure DevOps from the Bot Framework emulator when I run a test that fails
DCR: As a DevOps engineer, I want to have clear hinting when test failures occur so that I can notify the right team member to resolve the problem in the right way
DCR: As an NLU engineer, I would like to be able to test a bot using speech to ensure my custom speech models (if any) are working correctly for the targeted locales

DCR: As an NLU engineer, I want an easy to use website to create, read, update, and delete test transcript files so that I can collaborate with other non-developers on these transcripts in a managed/source-controlled way without having to download an IDE or know a language framework

DCR: As a DevOps engineer, I want to publish the live/latest NLU test results per-model and per-bot shared in a way so that I can point non-developers to a central location at any time for active status
DCR: As a DevOps engineer, I would like to have a tools in the Azure Marketplace that will allow me to configure and run NLU tests from the CI/CD pipeline
DCR: As an NLU engineer, I would like to run tests in different languages so I can ensure that my bot will work as expected in the targeted locales
